Shipping Administrator x 2 (PSG-SDC/201404/03/SG)
Job ID
EPM-00007554
Country
Singapore
State/Province
Singapore
City
Singapore
Publish Start Date
Apr 23 2014
Job Level
Experienced (Non-Manager)
|
Responsibilities:
Ensure all due urgent orders in SO Tools are picked and packed ready for shipment by the packing team.
Work with Packing staff to ensure orders are pack according the shipment cut-off timing.
Handle Checking of Orders according to ITC requirements.
Prepare shipping documents accordingly to company and country requirements.
Ensure products are ship correctly to their respective country of destination.
Deal with customer queries relating to shipping delays and documents discrepancy.
Handle General housekeeping by ensuring the work areas are free from all unwanted materials or foreign objects.
Perform any assignment being assigned by the Shipping Lead in related Shipping and Transportation activities.
Ensure filing of documents according to company document retention policy.
Requirements:
Diploma/Degree in Supply Chain or related discipline with 2 years experience within a computerized AS/400 Distribution Centre Environment preferably using JD Edwards Business System.
Experience within a distribution centre an advantage.
Knowledge of freight management and preparing of shipping documents will be an added advantage.
Good written and verbal communication skills.
Must have methodical/structured way of working and capable of organizing work/tasks.